    "body": "### Problem\n\nwhen use `Esc` to close picker windows, I got following errors.\n\n```\nE5108: Lua: D:\\wsdjeg\\picker.nvim/lua/picker/windows.lua:164: WinEnter Autocommands for \"*\": Vim(append):Lua callback: D:\\bundle_dir\\wsdjeg\\scrollbar.nvim/lua/scrollbar/init.lua:124: E242: Can't split a window while closing another\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_open_win'\n\tD:\\bundle_dir\\wsdjeg\\scrollbar.nvim/lua/scrollbar/init.lua:124: in function 'show'\n\tD:\\bundle_dir\\wsdjeg\\scrollbar.nvim/lua/scrollbar/init.lua:162: in function <D:\\bundle_dir\\wsdjeg\\scrollbar.nvim/lua/scrollbar/init.lua:161>\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_win_close'\n\tD:\\wsdjeg\\picker.nvim/lua/picker/windows.lua:164: in function <D:\\wsdjeg\\picker.nvim/lua/picker/windows.lua:160>\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_win_close'\n\tD:\\wsdjeg\\picker.nvim/lua/picker/windows.lua:164: in function <D:\\wsdjeg\\picker.nvim/lua/picker/windows.lua:160>\n\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nvim.pack.add({src = 'https://github.com/wsdjeg/picker.nvim'})\nvim.pack.add({src = 'https://github.com/wsdjeg/scrollbar.nvim'})\nrequire('picker').setup()\n```\n\n1. open a long file, make sure scrollbar is open, for example `:e doc\\windows.txt`\n2. `:Picker files`\n3. press `Esc`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nne errors when close floating windows.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nwin 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwt.exe\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nno\n\n### Installation\n\nscoop install neovim-nightly",
