            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yeah, it's not possible to split windows in some cases. `:h E242`  \nOpening a window (float or not) has the semantics of splitting from an existing window, which applies to `nvim_open_win`.\n\nE242 is from checking `split_disallowed` (from Vim 8.1.1756), which was looks like it was added to avoid cases where autocommands could mess up window frames. What's unclear is if it prevents other issues, though. (Details are sparse)\n\nThat said, opening a new _float_ ought not to touch the frames, so relaxing the check in that case _might_ be fine? (`b_locked_split` should still be checked, though)",
